\title{INLAocc: Occupancy Models via Integrated Nested Laplace Approximation}
\description{
Fits single-species, multi-species, spatial, temporal, integrated, and spatially-varying coefficient occupancy models using Integrated Nested Laplace Approximations (INLA). Provides a fast alternative to MCMC-based frameworks like 'spOccupancy', with a compatible API including mixed-model random effects syntax, posterior predictive checks, WAIC, k-fold cross-validation, and design-matrix prediction. Uses an EM algorithm with INLA at each M-step for the two-process (occupancy/detection) likelihood.
